19931218000000000_3	The case arose after documents from the former East Germany were uncovered by the Japanese media forcing the Ministry of International Trade and Industry to investigate Toshiba s alleged exports of leading edge semiconductor equipment from December 1986 to February 1987.	case aros document former east germani uncov japanes media forc ministri intern trade industri investig toshiba alleg export lead edg semiconductor equip decemb februari
19931218000000000_4	Miti officials said Toshiba exported masks and 150 silicon wafers to East Germany as well as providing documents detailing the production of advanced memory chips.	miti offici said toshiba export mask silicon wafer east germani well provid document detail product advanc memori chip
19931218000000000_5	The case is embarrassing for the Japanese government which claimed that it maintained tight controls over exports of strategic technologies.	case embarrass japanes govern claim maintain tight control export strateg technolog
19931218000000000_6	However Miti s punishment is relatively lenient as the 27 countries include Mongolia Vietnam and North Korea none of which is a leading importer of Japanese semiconductor products.	howev miti punish rel lenient countri includ mongolia vietnam north korea none lead import japanes semiconductor product
19931218000000000_7	China is the only significant market temporarily closed to Toshiba.	china onli signific market temporarili close toshiba
19931218000000000_8	Miti officials also reprimanded Mitsui the trading house which was involved in collecting payments for the deal.	miti offici also reprimand mitsui trade hous wa involv collect payment deal
19931218000000000_9	As is customary in such cases Mitsui said its employees had acted without authorisation and that two officials had been reprimanded.	customari case mitsui said employe act without authoris two offici reprimand
19931218000000000_10	The Japanese government has imposed penalties in 10 cases of Cocom violations and Miti said the export ban imposed on Toshiba was thought appropriate because the statute of limitations had expired for a criminal action against the company.	japanes govern ha impos penalti case cocom violat miti said export ban impos toshiba wa thought appropri becaus statut limit expir crimin action compani
19931218000000000_11	Toshiba estimates that its semiconductor exports to the 27 countries in an average month total Y1.	toshiba estim semiconductor export countri averag month total
19931218000000000_12	Total exports of chips this year will be around Y280bn.	total export chip thi year around bn
